news.title: US: Single family housing sees a rise in permits in January
news.para: Single-family housing starts, which account for the bulk of homebuilding, dropped 4.7% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.004 million units last month, the Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Friday.

news.title: Seven Gurugram civic body engineers allowed illegal buildings near ammo depot & Sadar Bazar, finds probe
news.para: MCG commissioner Narhari Singh Banger has now recommended action under Rule 7 (major penalty) of the Haryana Civil Services (Punishment and Appeal) Rules, 2016, against the accused engineers to the urban local bodies (ULB) department.

news.title: MIDC in final stage of acquiring 348 hectares land at two sites in Nashik
news.para: MIDC has set the target of acquiring land by April-end so that the work of preparing the layout and tender process for creating infrastructure would be started at the earliest.

news.title: Tambaram residents raise grievances over inaccuracies in property details
news.para: We got demand notices with inaccurate details despite the self declaration form for tax payments. We are not able to rectify this. The civic body has not been responsive,” resident Ganesh Venkatraman said.

news.title: GIS survey for property tax to be completed soon: Dehradun civic body
news.para: The project started from Kaulagarh in December 2021 and was expected to be complete within two years. However, actual number of properties in Dehradun exceeded initial estimate of 3.6 lakh resulting in a year’s extension.

news.title: Irregularities in sand mining led to loss of Rs 172 crore in Telangana:CAG
news.para: The audit sample included three selected project offices of Telangana State Mineral Development Corporation Ltd (TSMDCL) in Jayashankar Bhupalpally, Bhadradri Kothagudem and Karimnagar.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to reject building plans without parking spot
news.para: The move came considering the current situation where several houses, particularly individual buildings, don’t have enough parking space on their premises resulting in the vehicles being parked on public roads leading to congestion.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body cracks down on owners of 1,012 properties over tax default
news.para: The PCMC officials aim to take similar action against around 500 more properties till March 31, 2024, and have urged citizens to pay their pending dues to avoid the same.

news.title: China: Logan Group's liquidation proceedings dismissed
news.para: Regulatory bodies seem to have exerted greater pressure on banks to extend credit to property developers, accelerating the whitelist project process beyond anticipations," remarked Raymond Cheng, the head of China research at CGS International.

news.title: Prime minister lays foundation stone of Gurugram metro
news.para: The project, with a total length of 28.5 km, will connect Millennium City Centre to Udyog Vihar Phase-5 and merge in the existing metro network of Rapid Metro Rail Gurugram at Moulsari Avenue station near Cyber City.

news.title: BSNL, MTNL nudged to monetise land faster to pare debt
news.para: Cabinet secretary Rajiv Gauba called a review meeting with the senior officials of BSNL and MTNL earlier this week to take an update of the monetisation process. “They have been asked to prepare a detailed circle-wise report, with land parcel and reason for the delay or possible hurdles, by May 31,” another official said.

news.title: Cabinet note on Suraksha Group’s Wish Town plan likely soon
news.para: Once the cabinet note is cleared, the Yamuna Expressway Authority (YXPA) which has administrative control over the land will convey its position to the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT). The resolution plan is awaiting clearance at the tribunal.

news.title: Bengaluru development body holding mela on Feb 17 to sell 1,000 flats
news.para: Interested people can pay the initial deposit by demand drafts or online transfer for the flats they wish to purchase and receive allotment letters on the spot.

news.title: Cops to serve notice to Orris Group after FIR over funds diversion
news.para: A senior officer told TOI that the builder would be issued a notice and asked to join the investigation to speed up the investigation in the pending forgery cases.

news.title: Adani Realty gets MSRDC's 24-acre Bandra Reclamation redevelopment project
news.para: Adani Realty, a subsidiary of the Adani Group, has emerged as the top bidder for the redevelopment of the Maharashtra State Road Development Corporation's (MSRDC) 24-acre land at Bandra Reclamation.

news.title: Bandhan Bank acquires 12 offices in Mumbai’s BKC for Rs 135 crore
news.para: Bandhan Bank, headquartered in Kolkata, has acquired 12 office spaces across two floors in a commercial tower located in Mumbai's Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC) for over Rs 135.64 crore.

news.title: Properties in Bengaluru to get digital ownership document: Karnataka CM
news.para: Siddaramaiah said additional non-tax resources of Rs 2,000 crore will be mobilised through revised advertisement policies and premium Floor Area Ratio (FAR) policy from this fiscal year.

news.title: Homebuyers of stuck projects in Gurugram meet Haryana RERA chairman
news.para: The chairman visited all the project sites after meeting the representatives, according to a statement. The projects in Sector 63A, 68, 95, 103, and 104 are being developed by Mahira developers, it said.

news.title: ED conducts fresh raids on Supreme Constructions, seizes shares, FDs worth Rs 13 crore
news.para: According to a statement, the central agency froze cash and FDs of more than Rs 30 crore in the searches carried out at 22 locations on February 7.

news.title: Delhi court extends interim bail to Supertech chairman by 30 days
news.para: Additional Sessions Judge Devender Kumar Jangala extended the relief noting that the genuineness of the medical reports submitted by his lawyer was not disputed.
